div.p:
During the war Uruguay obtained a small amount of arms and equipment under lend
                    lease. In June 1946 she submitted a request for a long list of military
                    equipment. In February 1948 the list was reduced and the items requested were
                    for equipment: 

1 regiment of infantry (less 2 battalions);

1 cavalry reconnaissance squadron, mechanized (less M3–A1 tank
                            companies);

1 artillery battalion 105mm Howitzers (less 2 batteries);

1 artillery battalion 105mm Howitzers (less 2 guns);

1 anti-aircraft artillery automatic weapon battalion, semi-mobile
                            (less 4 40mm guns);
